  24:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****                       ##### RCC specific features #####
  25:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****   ==============================================================================
  26:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****     [..]
  27:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****       After reset the device is running from Internal High Speed oscillator
  28:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****       (HSI 64MHz) and all peripherals are off except internal SRAM, BSEC, PWR, IAC,
  29:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****       RIFSC, RISAF and JTAG
  30:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****       (+) There is no pre-scaler on High speed (AHB) and Low speed (APB) buses;
  31:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****           all peripherals mapped on these buses are running at HSI speed.
  32:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****       (+) All GPIOs are in analog mode , except the JTAG pins which
  33:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****           are assigned to be used for debug purpose.
  34:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c **** 
  35:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****     [..]
  36:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****       Once the device started from reset, the user application has to:
  37:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****       (+) Configure the clock source to be used to drive the System clock
  38:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****           (if the application needs higher frequency/performance than HSI)
  39:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****       (+) Configure the CPU and System bus clock frequencies
  40:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****       (+) Configure the AHB and APB buses pre-scalers
  41:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****       (+) Enable the clock for the peripheral(s) to be used
  42:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****       (+) Configure the clock kernel source(s) for peripherals which clocks are not
  43:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****           derived from the System clock
ARM GAS  /tmp/ccBOikzD.s 			page 50


  44:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c **** 
  45:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****                       ##### RCC Limitations #####
  46:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****   ==============================================================================
  47:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****     [..]
  48:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****       A delay between an RCC peripheral clock enable and the effective peripheral
  49:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****       enabling should be taken into account in order to manage the peripheral read/write
  50:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****       from/to registers.
  51:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****       (+) This delay depends on the peripheral mapping.
  52:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****       (+) If peripheral is mapped on AHB: the delay is 2 AHB clock cycle
  53:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****           after the clock enable bit is set on the hardware register
  54:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****       (+) If peripheral is mapped on APB: the delay is 2 APB clock cycle
  55:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****           after the clock enable bit is set on the hardware register
  56:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c **** 
  57:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****     [..]
  58:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****       Implemented Workaround:
  59:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****       (+) For AHB & APB peripherals, a dummy read to the peripheral register has been
  60:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****           inserted in each __HAL_RCC_PPP_CLK_ENABLE() macro.
  61:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c **** 
  62:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****     [..]
  63:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****       Incorrect APB prescaler setting:
  64:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****       (+) As described in the product errata, after enabling the bus clock to the
  65:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****       peripheral and changing the default APB prescaler setting, performing a
  66:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****       configuration on the bus peripheral does not update the peripheral registers,
  67:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****       resulting in unexpected behavior.
  68:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c **** 
  69:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****   @endverbatim
  70:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****   */
