1301:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****   * @brief  Enable the HSE Clock Security System.
1302:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****   * @note   If a failure is detected on the HSE oscillator clock, this oscillator
1303:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****   *         is automatically disabled and an interrupt is generated to inform the
1304:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****   *         software about the failure (Clock Security System Interrupt, CSSI),
1305:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****   *         allowing the MCU to perform rescue operations. The CSSI is linked to
1306:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****   *         the Cortex-M NMI (Non-Mask-able Interrupt) exception vector.
1307:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****   * @note   The HSE Clock Security System may be enabled even if the HSE is not enabled
1308:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****   *         but will be activated when the HSE is enabled and ready.
1309:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****   * @note   It is not possible to disable the HSE Clock Security System.
1310:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****   * @retval None
1311:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****   */
1312:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c **** void HAL_RCC_EnableCSS(void)
